headline: Chewy Stock Fetches Higher RS Rating At 81
summary: On Monday, Chewy stock reached a noteworthy technical benchmark, with its Relative Strength (RS) Rating climbing into the 80-plus percentile with an improvement to 81, a rise from 75 the day before.  IBD's unique RS Rating identifies technical performance by using a 1 (worst) to 99 (best) score that identifies how a stock's price performance over the trailing 52 weeks matches up against other publicly traded companies.
